When an image is being hotlinked from an external site, it is currently not possible to thumbnail that image. If we manually insert the thumbnail syntax in Text mode:
{code:none}
!<image-url>|thumbnail!
{code}
It will not work and will return:
{quote}Can only create thumbnails for attached images
{quote}

It would be great if this can be achieved as some users would prefer not to having manually download from the external site, and re-upload the image again. Not only it will reduce the effort spent just to link images, it will reduce the space used by {{$JIRA_HOME/data/attachments}} directory as well.

Since components are used _to group issues within a project into smaller parts_ ([https://confluence.atlassian.com/jirasoftwarecloud/organizing-work-with-components-764478279.html]), or even _to add some structure to projects, breaking it up into features, teams, modules, subprojects, and more_ ([https://www.atlassian.com/blog/jira-software/organize-jira-issues-subcomponents]), it would be very useful to show activity and statistics for any component.

Moreover, such a summary would be even more useful if it can possibly be referred to with a clean URL such as:
{quote}{{_baseUrl_/projects/_projectKey_/components/_componentName/summary_}}
{quote}
just like it is already possible for project:
{quote}{{_baseUrl_/projects/_projectKey_/summary}}
{quote}
as component can not be specifically referred to with an URL at the moment. (Project's components can be browsed (JRASERVER-12373) with:
{quote}{{_baseUrl_/projects/_projectKey_/components}}
{quote}
and component's issues can be browsed with JQL query URL.)

h3. Summary

When admins log in to Find New Apps, they will be greeted with the featured apps carousel which rotates around. It may be kind of distracting for some admins.

h3. Suggestions

Ability to disable the carousel.

h3. Workaround

Hide the section using CSS via Announcement Banner
{code:html}
<!-- Hide Apps Carousel -->
<style type="text/css">
ul.cloud-carousel{
    display: none !important;
}
</style>
{code}

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-41654].
  {panel}

Currently Audit log does not log any changes to the global list of Statuses. (JIRA _Administration > Issues > Statuses).

h4. Summary

Please add the following section to [Jira 7.13 upgrade notes|https://confluence.atlassian.com/jirasoftware/jira-software-7-13-x-upgrade-notes-957135908.html]

{quote}

h4. Proxy Server

Some odd behavior regarding user sessions is observed where we see a 404 error using REST API, randomly with a different account ID and session ID, etc after Jira is upgraded from 7.6 to 7.13. This is because some proxy servers like NGINX can act as a caching proxy. In order to prevent the user session issues, NGINX cache needs to be cleared during the Jira upgrade process. 
{quote}

h3. Issue Summary

{{CustomisedConfigurationsHealthCheck}} failed, the instance showed Johnson page about modifications in setenv.sh. Any request issued to the instance ended with HTTP 503. Meanwhile, querying "_/status_" endpoint returned "_Running_" status. 
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Modify the HealthCheck to always fail
 # See the Johnson page or issue a REST call
 # query the "_/status_" endpoint

h3. Expected Results

When Johnson page is shown and the instance is not working, /status should never return a "RUNNING" state.
h3. Actual Results
{noformat}
// 20191211194005
// https://jira-localhost/status{
  "state": "RUNNING"
}
{noformat}
h3. Workaround

I don't think there's a stable workaround. Technically, one could ping an endpoint other than /status, but that would possibly break under other circumstances.

h3. Problem Definition

When an issue has a resolution set, it's not displayed strikethrough in "Issues in Epic" as it's in boards and normal links as seen on the screenshot below:
 * !Screen Shot 2019-12-03 at 12.01.21.png|thumbnail!

h3. Suggested Solution

Implement the ability to have the strikethrough in the "Issues in Epic" panel in order to follow the same pattern as the "Issue links" panel.
h3. Workaround

It may be possible to use a front-end workaround, depending on your Jira version. 

The following code was tested on Jira 7.13.9 and 8.5.3. Since the Jira front-end code is subject to change at any time, it is possible that this workaround will stop working in the future. 

+Workaround Steps+

# Place the following into the [Announcement Banner|https://confluence.atlassian.com/adminjiraserver/configuring-an-announcement-banner-938846985.html]
{code:java}
<script>
AJS.$(document).ready(function() {
console.log('JRASERVER-70347 Workaround Start');
    AJS.$('#ghx-issues-in-epic-table .jira-issue-status-lozenge-green').closest('.issuerow').css('text-decoration','line-through');
});</script> {code}
# Any Issue in the _Issues in Epic_ panel with a "Done" type status (green) will now be striked through.
